---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Bethany J. Curran is a modernization and transformation leader who builds frameworks, rewrites job descriptions, and solves problems no one has named yet."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="flex-1">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-16">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-4">About</p>
          <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl text-navy font-light leading-tight mb-6">
            Bethany J. Curran
          </h1>
          <p class="font-display text-2xl text-charcoal/60 italic mb-8">
            I accidentally fell into modernization<br/>by solving problems no one else had named.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bethanyjcurran/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="btn-primary"
          >
            Connect on LinkedIn
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none">
              <path d="M2 12L12 2M12 2H5M12 2V9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 -right-3 w-36 h-36 rounded-full border border-sage/30"></div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-4 -left-4 w-24 h-24 rounded-full bg-mustard/15"></div>
          <img
            src="/headshot.jpg"
            alt="Bethany J. Curran"
            class="relative z-10 w-full max-w-sm mx-auto md:ml-auto object-cover aspect-square rounded-sm shadow-lg"
          />
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-1 h-2/3 bg-terracotta rounded-sm -translate-x-3 z-10"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Impact stats bar -->
    <div class="bg-navy">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
          {[
            { value: '35%', label: 'Profit increase', sub: '$300K MRR service, 9 months' },
            { value: '3×',  label: 'Roles written', sub: 'from scratch, for unnamed problems' },
            { value: '2.5yr', label: 'Portfolio transformation', sub: 'end-to-end modernization' },
            { value: '10+', label: 'Years', sub: 'in systems modernization & leadership' },
          ].map((stat, i) => (
            <div class={i > 0 ? 'md:border-l md:border-cream/10 md:pl-8' : ''}>
              <p class="font-display text-4xl font-light text-mustard mb-1">{stat.value}</p>
              <p class="font-body text-sm text-cream font-medium mb-0.5">{stat.label}</p>
              <p class="font-body text-xs text-cream/50">{stat.sub}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Story -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="prose prose-oia max-w-none">
        <p class="section-label not-prose mb-6">The story</p>

        <p>
          I didn't set out to be a modernization leader. I set out to solve the problem in front of me —
          and kept doing it until I'd done it enough times that someone finally had a name for it.
        </p>

        <p>
          Three times in my career, I've walked into an organization with an ill-defined problem,
          sat in the work long enough to understand it, and written a job description that didn't exist
          before I got there. That's not a tactic. It's just what happens when you pay closer attention
          to what's broken than to what your title says.
        </p>

        <p>
          Most recently, I spent two and a half years modernizing an entire portfolio of technology services
          at a large MSP. I built a framework to fully map and address technical debt — then applied it to
          a $300K monthly recurring revenue service, producing a 35% profit increase in nine months.
          Then I applied the same methodology to the smaller services. Then the largest.
        </p>

        <p>
          My measure of success was the day my teams stopped needing me. I took a week off for my birthday,
          didn't check my phone once, and came back to silence. The sky didn't fall.
          That was the signal. My assignment was complete.
        </p>

        <p>
          My approach to modernization isn't primarily technical. It's organizational. Legacy systems become
          legacy because of how humans made decisions over time — the shortcuts, the incentives, the things
          no one wrote down. You can't fix the system without understanding the humans inside it.
          And you can't lead the humans through change without earning their trust first.
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm currently exploring what that next problem looks like — and whose organization I'll help
          modernize next. If yours has a problem that doesn't have a job title yet, I'd like to hear about it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Expertise -->
    <section class="bg-cream-dark/50 border-t border-b border-cream-dark">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
        <p class="section-label mb-10">Areas of expertise</p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          {[
            { title: 'Technical Debt Mapping', body: 'Building frameworks that make invisible debt visible — across tooling, processes, and systems.' },
            { title: 'Services Modernization', body: 'End-to-end portfolio transformation: architecture, workflow, team, and metrics.' },
            { title: 'Change Leadership', body: 'Guiding teams through transitions they don\'t see coming — and making it stick.' },
            { title: 'Organizational Design', body: 'Identifying roles that don\'t exist yet and building the structure around them.' },
            { title: 'MSP & Services Operations', body: 'Deep background in managed services: recurring revenue, SLAs, client relationships.' },
            { title: 'Engineering Leadership', body: 'Hiring, developing, and growing engineering teams through periods of significant change.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="bg-cream p-6 border border-cream-dark">
              <div class="w-6 h-0.5 bg-terracotta mb-4"></div>
              <h3 class="font-body text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase text-navy mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="font-body text-sm text-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">{item.body}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 text-center">
      <p class="font-display text-3xl text-navy font-light mb-6">
        Looking for someone who operates well in ambiguity?
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bethanyjcurran/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="btn-primary"
      >
        Let's connect
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Base>
